### 3. Suppress `cli setup` subprocess stdout during upgrade

**File:** `src/commands/cli/upgrade.ts` — `runSetupOnNewBinary()`

Add `--quiet` to the args list when spawning `cli setup`:

```typescript
const args = [
  "cli",
  "setup",
  "--quiet",          // ← suppress "Binary: Installed to..." output
  "--method",
  method,
  "--channel",
  channel,
  "--no-modify-path",
];
```

The `cli setup` command already supports `--quiet` (defined in setup.ts flags). The upgrade command prints its own success message via `CommandOutput`, making the setup output redundant.

